CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. A2 reads: " 'Move Back to 50 Feet' - is the order given by Judge of Elections Carl Lee on Tuesday to William A. Baker, candidate for committeeman in the 15th District. Mr. Lee acted after deputy sheriffs arrived to investigate complaints, and reminded the judge of elections that he must admit nobody but voters and watchers in the polls at 2132 Centre Ave.; also that spectators and workers must stay away from the entrance.  The crowd above is formed almost directly in front of the polls. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women gathered on sidewalk in front of 15th District polling place, 2132 Center Avenue, across from Elmore Street, Hill District
